      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, r u saying the guy from the urban area is more likely to be a \"risk to society\" just because he doesn't have a steady job or family ties? wouldnt his environment be seen as a mitigating factor instead of an aggravating one in a real court? i'm confused why he'd get a harsher sentence for being from a lower SES background.",
